---
import { WORKER_TOOLS } from "../model.ts";
---

<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-agents-heading">
  <h1 class="api-page-title" id="api-agents-heading">For agentic editors</h1>
  <p>
    A pipeline that edits video needs to branch on proof: which ranges are speech, in which
    language, where speakers overlap, which lines are evidence-backed and which were withheld, and
    what one exact span means. Each of those returns here as a receipt with lineage.
  </p>
  <p>
    Clients integrate at <code>/v1</code>; the models doing the work never see it. Workers get
    task-private, grant-scoped tools over ephemeral loopback bridges, and cannot mint capability,
    choose a path, or widen scope. The host stays the authority for identity, budgets, artifacts,
    and events.
  </p>
  <ul class="api-tools" aria-label="Grant-scoped worker tools">
    {WORKER_TOOLS.map((tool) => (
      <li>{tool}</li>
    ))}
  </ul>
  <p>Live translate guesses. This studies the media first, then hands your pipeline the study.</p>
</section>
